overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The assistant undertook a
  comprehensive design overhaul, starting with a new sleep-themed color palette
  using OKLCH for calming indigo/purple tones and teal accents. The main form
  layout was redesigned with subtle background elements, an enhanced progress
  indicator, and a thematic card header. All UI components like checkboxes,
  radio buttons, sliders, and cards received a polish with improved hover and
  selected states. The IntroSection was transformed into a more engaging welcome
  experience with feature cards. Crucially, all 14 questionnaire sections were
  updated to use consistent card-style groupings and theme-based typography. A
  console error related to null input values was also fixed. Finally, the
  ReportSection's inconsistent card header gradients were unified, and all
  hardcoded alert and text colors were replaced with the new theme variables,
  resulting in a cohesive, professional, and calming user interface.
